<h2> <span class="mw-headline" id="The_Profit_Maximizing_Rule">The Profit Maximizing Rule</span></h2>
<p>If <strong>MR &gt; MC</strong> then you should <strong>produce more</strong></p>
<p>If <strong>MR &lt; MC</strong> then you should <strong>produce less</strong></p>
<p>When <strong>MR = MC</strong> then you have the <strong>highest profits</strong></p>
<p>This is the rule that you will use to decide how much to produce and maximize profits</p>
<p>NOTE: This has a big assumption that the price has been kept constant, in the example at $8.00</p>

